headline: Coca-Cola makes a surprising change to its products
summary: For years, consumers have complained about shrinkflation. That’s when less of an item comes in a package, and the price either stays the same or goes up. Sometimes, companies attempt to do this sneakily. You buy a package of your favorite chips or a box of cookies, and there’s just less there. In ...
